  "text": "The concept of limiting the 3D visualization to a local region around a trajectory has been explored in recent research. Lampe et al. introduced the technique of curve-centric reformation [CITATION_1] . In their work, spatial curves through a volume were straightened, and the immediate volume around the curve was warped to match. In this way, the values surrounding the curve became easily visible while the shape of the curve was lost. Our work also focuses on showing curve-centric information, but we do so without deforming the volume or the curve.",
  "correct_citation": {
